com.percussion.cms.objectstore
Class PSCmsObject

java.lang.Object
  com.percussion.cms.objectstore.PSCmsObject
All Implemented Interfaces:
IPSCmsComponent, Cloneable
public class PSCmsObject
extends Object
implements IPSCmsComponent

An object representation of a row in the PSX_OBJECTS table. This object is immutable.

equals

public boolean equals(Object o)
Description copied from interface: IPSCmsComponent
Indicates whether some other object is "equal to" this one. All implementing classes must override this method as the default behavior is incorrect for deep clones. If the implementation does not follow the contract documented for this method in Object, then it must clearly state how it deviates from that contract. The following algorithm should be used:
  1. Call the base class (unless Object) and if true is returned, continue.
  2. Compare all members of current class.
  3. If all members are equal, return true.

Specified by:
equals in interface IPSCmsComponent
Overrides:
equals in class Object
Parameters:
o - the reference object with which to compare. May be null;
Returns:
true if this object is logically equivalent to the supplied obj; false otherwise. If null or not an instance of this class, false is returned.

hashCode

public int hashCode()
Description copied from interface: IPSCmsComponent
Must be overridden to fulfill contract of this method as described in Object. The following method should be used to calculate the hash code.
  1. Get the hashcode from the base class (unless the base class is Object).
  2. Add this hash code to the sum of all hash codes obtained from all non-native types.
  3. Add to this result the hash code obtained by creating a concatenated string of all native types and taking the hash code of that.

Specified by:
hashCode in interface IPSCmsComponent
Overrides:
hashCode in class Object
Returns:
A hash code value for this object that will work correctly for maps.
